Ssh-uri is a small wrapper for the ssh command.
It parses SSH URIs as defined in
https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-salowey-secsh-uri/
and invokes ssh with appropriate flags.

Examples:
	ssh-uri ssh://user@host.example.com
	ssh-uri ssh://user@host.example.com:2222

Todo:
